  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements</p><p>Roles & Responsibilities:<br /></p><p>Supervise Site Operations: Oversee daily work on-site, managing both sub-contractors and in-house workers to ensure tasks are completed on time and to the required standard.<br /></p><p>Ensure Safety Compliance: Make sure all safety protocols are followed, and all workers comply with Singapore’s Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) regulations.</p><p>Coordinate the Project: Work closely with the project manager and other teams to keep the project on track and meet deadlines.<br /></p><p>Monitor Work Quality: Check the quality of work and ensure it meets the project specifications and industry standards.<br /></p><p>Manage Workers: Provide clear instructions to workers, resolve issues, and ensure resources are used effectively.<br /></p><p>Report Progress: Keep accurate records of daily activities, material usage, and site conditions. Report progress to the project manager.</p><p>Ensure Timely Completion: Manage the work schedule to avoid delays and ensure work is finished on time.<br /></p><p>Lead Toolbox Meetings: Conduct daily meetings to discuss work priorities, safety, and any updates with the team.<br /></p><p>Conduct Site Inspections: Regularly inspect the site to ensure work follows the construction plans and report any issues.<br /></p><p>Coordinate with Contractors: Work with external contractors and vendors to ensure timely delivery of materials and services.<br /></p><p>Solve Problems: Address and resolve any issues that arise on-site, such as delays or safety concerns.<br /></p><p>Maintain Equipment: Ensure all equipment and tools are in good condition and report any problems to management.<br /></p><p>Manage Subcontractors: Oversee subcontractors’ work to make sure it meets the project’s standards and deadlines.<br /></p><p>Communicate with Clients: Keep clients and stakeholders updated on progress and address any concerns they may have.<br /></p><p>Requirements:<br /></p><p>Experience: At least 2 years of experience in construction, preferably in a supervisory role.<br /></p><p>Skills: Strong communication and leadership skills, with the ability to solve problems and manage a team effectively.<br /></p><p>Knowledge: Experience in structural steel work is a plus.<br /></p><p>Physical Fitness: Ability to handle the physical demands of working on-site.</p>",
